text: Robe is an unincorporated community in Snohomish County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Robe was established in 1894, and remained in operation until 1954. The community bears the name of a local pioneer. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Snohomish County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Robe, Washington
